{
  "texts": [
    "❷ R*tree: the R*-tree index [9] that optimizes the R-tree structure by minimizing the leaf node overlap.",
    "❸ STRTree: the R-tree index with the sort-tile-recursive (STR) bulk-loading strategy [46].",
    "For both R*tree and STRTree, we adopt the implementations from the Boost Geometry Library [12].",
    "The R-tree node capacity is set to 128 according to a recent benchmark [66].",
    "❹ kdtree: the kd-tree index [10] that recursively partitions the space by the median of each dimension in a roundrobin fashion."
  ]
}